*                            DT_COST.SIZ
*==============================================================================
*
*  MBS                                SI UNITS
*
*  Part    - 8 character part name used to identify the different parts
*  Name      in the data files & BOM. For rigid frames, just enter FRAME.
*
*  Sup     - Integer value that references the Supplier file which
*  Id        describes the supplier & discount factors for the part.
*
*  Part    - 2 character description of the part color. If no color
*  Color     enter -- or NO. If a part cost for any color is the same,
*            enter CO rather than list all the individual colors.
*            Special color numbers for panels include:
*
*  Cost    - 2 character description of how the cost factors are to be
*  Unit      applied.
*              M  - The cost is based on the part length.(M =mtr)
*              EA - The cost is based on a the quantity.
*              KG - The cost is to be based on the weight.
*
*  Material- The material cost of the part.
*  Cost
*
*  Labor   - The cost of labor for fabricating the part.
*  Cost
*
*  Min     - Describes a minimum unit for determining cost.
*  Unit        M  - This is the minimum length of the part that is used
*                   for the cost calculation. If this value is 3.00, but
*                   the actual part length is 2.50, use the 3.00 for cost
*                   calculations.
*              EA - This is the minimum number of parts that are used for
*                   the cost calculations. If this value is 100.0, but the
*                   actual part quantity is 89, the program will use 100 for
*                   the cost calculations.
*              KG - This is the minimum weight of parts that are used for
*                   the cost calculations. If this value is 100.0, but the
*                   actual part weight is 89, the program will use 100 for
*                   the cost calculations.
*
* Extra    - Describes additional charges for the part based on the cost
* Min,Max    unit if that unit is less than or greater than some value.
*              M  - If the part is shorter than the minimum length, or
*                   longer than a maximum length.
*              EA - If the part quantity is less than the minimum number, or
*                   greater than a maximum number.
*              KG - If the part weighs less than or greater than the
*                   minimum or maximum value.
*
*                    ----Standard_Charges-----  ------Additional_Charges------
*                          Matrl  Labor                Extra_Min      Extra_Max
* Part    Sup  Part  Cost   Cost   Cost   Min   Cost   Unit  Cost    Unit  Cost
* Name     Id  Clr   Unit FL/unit FL/unit  Unit  Unit    mm  FL      m     FL
*-------  ---  ----  ----  -----  -----  -----  ----  ----- -----  ------ -----
